Package: python3-flask-security
Source: flask-security
Version: 1.7.5-2
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Debian Python Modules Team <python-modules-team@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Installed-Size: 133
Depends: python3-flask (>= 0.9), python3-flask-login, python3-flask-mail, python3-flask-principal, python3-flaskext.wtf, python3-itsdangerous, python3-passlib, python3:any (>= 3.3.2-2~)
Section: python
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/mattupstate/flask-security
Description: Simple security for Flask apps (Python 3)
 Flask-Security allows you to quickly add common security mechanisms
 to your Flask application. They include:
 .
   * Session based authentication
   * Role management
   * Password encryption
   * Basic HTTP authentication
   * Token based authentication
   * Token based account activation (optional)
   * Token based password recovery / resetting (optional)
   * User registration (optional)
   * Login tracking (optional)
   * JSON/Ajax Support
 .
 This is the Python 3 version of the package.
